Portions of this software are derived from the MentraOS Camera Example App
template, originally published by Mentra Community at:
https://github.com/Mentra-Community/MentraOS-Camera-Example-App

The MentraOS template provided the initial Bun/TypeScript app-server scaffold,
MentraOS SDK integration patterns, and camera-session wiring that Reflections
extends with live streaming, perception, memory, and proactivity.

Reflections also vendors and depends on third-party software, including but
not limited to:

  - LR-ASD (Lightweight and Robust Active Speaker Detection)
    https://github.com/Junhua-Liao/LR-ASD — MIT License.
    Vendored under packages/third_party/lr_asd/ for active speaker detection.

  - InsightFace MobileFaceNet (ArcFace, w600k_mbf) for face embedding.
  - OpenCV YuNet (Apache 2.0) for face detection.
  - MediaMTX (MIT) for WHIP/WHEP streaming.
  - Qwen3-1.7B base model (Apache 2.0) and the Reflections LoRA adapter.

